text: Love the prawn noodles and their Mee Siam. Nonya style ..delicious and fresh.  Love their fried wontons too . I have been following them from Roxy , Katong to Kaki Bukit.

Ordered one prawn yellow-mee / bee hoon noodle soup (6/10 rating) & one dry version (7/10 rating).

Strong point is value for money for 4 local bucks per small bowl. Large bowl is an additional dollar.

Soup is a tad too sweet.

Other than that I will repeat my visit if in need of my shrimp (prawn) noodles fix.

Delicious, affordable and fresh!
Love the prawn noodles, its just what I like. The wonton is good too, $2 for 3 pieces. Will try the other stuff in the menu
